Problem Statement 1

Problem Statement :
“The anticipation, recognition and appraisal of a crime risk and the initiation of some action to remove or reduce it.”
Dallas, a modern metropolis in north Texas, is a commercial and cultural hub of the region. it is the ninth most-populous city in the US and the third-largest in Texas after Houston and San Antonio.  The Dallas crime rate is higher than more than 90 percent of U.S. cities, which means that citizens and tourists in Dallas are more prone to become victims.? According to Neighborhood Scout's analysis of FBI reported crime data, your chance of becoming a victim of one of these crimes in Dallas is one in 129. your chance of becoming a victim of a property crime is one in 30, which is a rate of 34 per one thousand population.
